# Screen Structure

Use the shared `Screen` component and `useHeader` hook for consistent layout and navigation across screens.

## Screen Component

Wrap screen content in `Screen` from `@/components/Screen`:

```tsx
import { Screen } from "@/components/Screen"

export default function MyScreen() {
  return (
    <Screen preset="scroll">
      {/* content */}
    </Screen>
  )
}
```

**Presets:**
- `scroll` – Scrollable content; use when content may overflow (default for most screens)
- `fixed` – Non-scrolling; use for short, fixed layouts
- `auto` – Enables scroll only when content exceeds viewport

## Header via useHeader

Use `useHeader` from `@/utils/useHeader` for screen headers. Call it at the top of the component:

```tsx
import { useHeader } from "@/utils/useHeader"
import { router } from "expo-router"

export default function MyScreen() {
  useHeader({
    titleTx: "recipeListScreen:title",
    leftIcon: "back",
    onLeftPress: () => router.back(),
    rightTx: "common:save",
    onRightPress: handleSave,
  })

  return <Screen preset="scroll">...</Screen>
}
```

**Common props:** `titleTx` / `title`, `leftIcon`, `onLeftPress`, `rightText` / `rightTx`, `onRightPress`, `RightActionComponent`. Prefer `titleTx` and `rightTx` over plain text (per i18n rule).
